				\begin{document}$$ \lambda_{i} = {\raise0.7ex\hbox{${\left( {{\text{D}}_{{\text{i}}} - \alpha } \right)}$} \!\mathord{\left/ {\vphantom {{\left( {{\text{D}}_{{\text{i}}} - \alpha } \right)} {\sum\nolimits_{{\text{i = 1}}}^{{\text{n}}} {{\text{D}}_{{\text{i}}} - \alpha } }}}\right.\kern-\nulldelimiterspace} \!\lower0.7ex\hbox{${\sum\nolimits_{{\text{i = 1}}}^{{\text{n}}} {{\text{D}}_{{\text{i}}} - \alpha } }$}} $$\end{document}λi=Di-α∑i = 1nDi-αwhere λi is the weight of station I, Di is the station distance to the unknown point, and α is the weighting power.

